info.title: Eventbrite
info.description: Eventbrite is the leading web-based solution for creating, managing, and promoting local events.

parameters.name: amount_off
parameters.description: The fixed amount off the ticket price. Each discount code can have a fixed discount amount or a variable (percentage) discount amount, but not both.

parameters.name: code
parameters.description: The discount code. Spaces, apostrophes and non-alphanumeric characters are not allowed, except for dashes and underscores. Examples: u201cearlybirdspecial_08u2033, u201cmembersonlyu201d, u201cdc121232u2033.

parameters.name: data-type
parameters.description: xml or json data-types are supported

parameters.name: end_date
parameters.description: The discount end date and time, in ISO 8601 format (e.g., u201c2007-12-31 23:59:59u2033).

parameters.name: event_id
parameters.description: The event ID. The event must have been previously created using /event_new.

parameters.name: percent_off
parameters.description: The percentage off the ticket price. Each discount code can have a fixed discount amount or a variable (percentage) discount amount, but not both.

parameters.name: quantity_available
parameters.description: Maximum number of times this discount can be used. If not provided, no maximum is set.

parameters.name: start_date
parameters.description: The discount start date and time, in ISO 8601 format (e.g., u201c2007-12-31 23:59:59u2033).

parameters.name: tickets
parameters.description: Comma-separated list of ticket IDs for which the discount applies. If not provided, the discount will apply to all ticket types.

parameters.name: personalized_url
parameters.description: The event registration URL. If you pass u201ctesteventu201d, the event will be accessible at u201chttp://testevent.eventbrite.comu201d. This string is limited to 255 characters max. Optional.

parameters.name: privacy
parameters.description: 0 for a private event, 1 for a public event. If not provided, will default to 0. Optional.

parameters.name: start_date
parameters.description: The event start date and time, in ISO 8601 format (e.g., u201c2007-12-31 23:59:59u2033).

parameters.name: status
parameters.description: The event status. Allowed values are u201cdraftu201d, u201cliveu201d for new events. If not provided, status will be u201cdraftu201d, meaning that the event registration page will not be available publicly. Optional.

parameters.name: text_color
parameters.description: Custom hexadecimal color for your registration page. Format: FFFFFF *without* the pound. Optional.

parameters.name: timezone
parameters.description: The event time zone in relation to GMT (e.g., u201cGMT+01u2033, u201cGMT+02u2033, u201cGMT-01u2033).

parameters.name: venue_id
parameters.description: The event venue ID. The venue must have been previously created using /venue_new. Optional.

parameters.name: address
parameters.description: The venue address. Optional.

parameters.name: category
parameters.description: Event categories (comma seperated): conference, conventions, entertainment, fundraisers, meetings, other, performances, reunions, sales, seminars, social, sports, tradeshows, travel, religion, fairs, food, music, recreation. Optional.

parameters.name: city
parameters.description: The venue city. Optional.

parameters.name: country
parameters.description: 2-letter country code, according to the ISO 3166 format. Optional.

parameters.name: count_only
parameters.description: Only return the total number of events (u201ctrueu201d or u201cfalseu201d). Default is u201cfalseu201d. Optional.

parameters.name: data-type
parameters.description: xml or json data-types are supported

parameters.name: date
parameters.description: The event start date. Limit the list of results to a date range, specified by a label or by exact dates. Currently supported labels include: u201cAllu201d, u201cFutureu201d, u201cPastu201d, u201cTodayu201d, u201cYesterdayu201d, u201cLast Weeku201d, u201cThis Weeku201d, u201cNext weeku201d, u201cThis Monthu201d, u201cNext Monthu201d and months by name, e.g. u201cOctoberu201d. Exact date ranges take the form u201cYYYY-MM-DD YYYY-MM-DDu201d, e.g. u201c2008-04-25 2008-04-27u2033. Optional.

parameters.name: date_created
parameters.description: The date range the event was created, specified by a label or by exact dates. Currently supported labels include: u201cAllu201d, u201cFutureu201d, u201cPastu201d, u201cTodayu201d, u201cYesterdayu201d, u201cLast Weeku201d, u201cThis Weeku201d, u201cNext weeku201d, u201cThis Monthu201d, u201cNext Monthu201d and months by name, e.g. u201cOctoberu201d. Exact date ranges take the form u201cYYYY-MM-DD YYYY-MM-DDu201d, e.g. u201c2008-04-25 2008-04-27u2033. Optional.

parameters.name: date_modified
parameters.description: The date range the event was modified, specified by a label or by exact dates. Currently supported labels include: u201cAllu201d, u201cFutureu201d, u201cPastu201d, u201cTodayu201d, u201cYesterdayu201d, u201cLast Weeku201d, u201cThis Weeku201d, u201cNext weeku201d, u201cThis Monthu201d, u201cNext Monthu201d and months by name, e.g. u201cOctoberu201d. Exact date ranges take the form u201cYYYY-MM-DD YYYY-MM-DDu201d, e.g. u201c2008-04-25 2008-04-27u2033. Optional.

parameters.name: keywords
parameters.description: The search keywords. To run an OR search, you need this format: u201ckeywords=google%20OR%20multimediau201d. Optional.

parameters.name: latitude
parameters.description: If u201cwithinu201d is set you can limit your search to wgs84 coordinates (latitude, longitude). Optional.

parameters.name: longitude
parameters.description: If u201cwithinu201d is set you can limit your search to wgs84 coordinates (latitude, longitude). Optional.

parameters.name: max
parameters.description: Limit the number of events returned. Maximum limit is 100 events per page. Default is 10. Optional.

parameters.name: organizer
parameters.description: The organizer name. Optional.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: Allows for paging through the results of a query. Default is 1. Optional.

parameters.name: postal_code
parameters.description: The postal/zip code of the venue. Optional.

parameters.name: region
parameters.description: The venue state/province/county/territory depending on the country. 2-letter state code is required for US addresses. Optional.

parameters.name: since_id
parameters.description: Returns events with id greater than u201csince_idu201d value. Default is 1. Optional.

parameters.name: sort_by
parameters.description: Sort the list of events by u201cidu201d, u201cdateu201d, u201cnameu201d, u201ccityu201d. The default is u201cdateu201d. Optional.

parameters.name: tracking_link
parameters.description: The tracking link code to add to the event URLs. Optional.

parameters.name: within
parameters.description: If u201cwithinu201d is set and the u201ccityu201d or u201czipcodeu201d resolve to a specific geolocation, the search will be restricted to the specified within radius. The sorting default will be set to u201cdistanceu201d. Optional.

parameters.name: within_unit
parameters.description: If within is set, you can specify the unit to use: u201cMu201d for miles, or u201cKu201d for kilometers. By default, the API will use miles. Optional.
